critique: This executive order pertains to the inspection of income tax returns by the Department of Commerce, in accordance with rules and regulations prescribed by the Secretary of the Treasury. It seems primarily concerned with inter-agency cooperation and information sharing. There's no immediately obvious indication of a strong ideological tilt, immigration stance, expansion of executive power, or a shift in federalism. It doesn't directly address national security vs. civil liberties, economic regulation, or social inclusion. Therefore, initial scores will be close to neutral across most axes.
